The independent passes converged on one serious product defect: the backend calls `received_by_user`/`created_by_user` an `assigned_owner`. A portal-created application can therefore appear to staff as if the borrower is the current internal owner—exactly the invented ownership 005I4 was meant to remove. I also confirmed three contract/test gaps: portal detail omits nominee ID/minor status, both application forms reimplement the adult-age rule in React, and blocked PATCH/portal nominee paths plus the real async detail component are not exercised.

I’ll queue one focused 005I5 corrective slice for those 005I3/005I4 regressions. Separately, I’ll sharpen 006D2B to close the remaining architecture seam issues (static import-boundary proof and configuration/credit dependency direction) while it performs the already-planned loan-limit extraction.
Review window and independent critics are complete. Confirmed owner synthesis plus nominee/frontend/test gaps require a corrective slice; architecture seam corrections fit the already-queued 006D2B.
